The Honey Baked Ham Company has named Deborah Derby chief executive officer, according to the company’s LinkedIn page. Her appointment comes on the heels of Jim Dinkins’ retirement after five years in the role.&nbsp;

Derby most recently served as president and CEO of Carrols Restaurant Group, which was Burger King’s largest franchisee in the United States with more than 1,000 locations and a total enterprise value of $1 billion. In early 2025, Burger King parent company Restaurant Brands International acquired Carrols for approximately $1 billion in an all-cash transaction.&nbsp;

Prior to leading Carrols, Derby served as chief administrative officer of The Children’s Place, president of Horizon Group USA, and executive vice president at Toys R Us. Earlier in her career, she held several roles at Whirlpool Corporation. She earned her law degree at Notre Dame.

Honey Baked Ham has nearly 450 locations in the United States, according to Technomic. The company ended 2024 with more than $402 million in sales. It was recently named the No. 4 chain overall on Technomic’s America’s Favorite Chains list, scoring high for food and beverage quality.&nbsp;

“The appeal for Honey Baked Ham is it is associated with a traditional retail product and they’re selling that quality in a sandwich form. It seems niche, but people strongly associate it with that retail product and give them credit for quality,” Technomic director of consumer and industry insights Robert Byrne&nbsp;said in an interview.&nbsp;

